# Product Requirements Document — EU Solicit

**Author:** Deb  
**Date:** 2026-04-23  
**Version:** 2.0 (Canonical — synthesised from Epics 1–12 implementation record)  
**Status:** Final

---

## 1. Executive Summary

EU Solicit is a full-stack SaaS platform that helps companies, municipalities, and consulting firms win European Union public procurement contracts and EU grant funding. It combines automated opportunity discovery, AI-driven document intelligence, collaborative proposal authoring, compliance management, and subscription billing into a single, multi-tenant product.

The platform is targeted at the Bulgarian and broader EU market. Users can move from "opportunity identified" to "compliant proposal submitted" within a single product without switching between spreadsheets, portals, or separate document tools. The AI layer — powered by the KraftData platform — handles the heavy lifting: parsing 200-page tender packages, generating first-draft proposals, pre-checking compliance, and predicting evaluator scores.

**Elevator pitch:** "Google for EU tenders, with a co-pilot that writes your bid."

---

## 2. Product Vision and Goals

### 2.1 Vision Statement

To become the trusted AI-powered operating system for EU procurement and grant teams — making it as easy to win a European public contract as it is to complete an e-commerce checkout.

### 2.2 Business Goals

| Goal | Target | Horizon |
|------|--------|---------|
| Registered companies | 100 | MVP launch |
| Active paid subscribers | 25 | MVP launch |
| Free → paid conversion | 10% | MVP launch |
| Trial → paid conversion | 25% | MVP launch |
| Proposals generated via platform | 200 | MVP launch |
| NPS score | ≥ 40 | 90 days post-launch |

### 2.3 Problem Statement

EU public procurement and grant applications are notoriously complex:

- Tenders are published across dozens of portals in multiple languages.
- Compliance documents (ESPD, technical specifications, mandatory annexes) run to hundreds of pages.
- Multi-user bid teams lack purpose-built collaboration tools.
- Win rates are low and improving requires structured lessons-learned processes.
- SMEs and mid-market firms cannot afford the advisory fees of large consulting firms.

EU Solicit directly addresses each of these pain points through automation and AI.

---

## 3. Users and Personas

### 3.1 Primary Personas

| Persona | Description | Key Needs |
|---------|-------------|-----------|
| **Bid Manager** | Leads tender submissions for a company; owns the overall bid process | Pipeline visibility, task orchestration, approval workflows, AI drafts |
| **Technical Writer** | Authors the technical sections of proposals | Rich text editor, AI assistance, version control, section locking |
| **Financial Analyst** | Builds cost models and budgets for bids | Pricing assistant, budget builder, EU cost category compliance |
| **Legal Reviewer** | Reviews contracts and compliance clauses | Clause risk flagging, ESPD auto-fill, compliance framework validation |
| **Company Admin** | Manages team access, billing, and company profile | RBAC management, billing portal, company profile vault |
| **Platform Admin** | Internal EU Solicit staff managing tenants, crawlers, and frameworks | Admin portal (VPN-restricted), tenant management, crawler scheduling |

### 3.2 Organisational Context

- **Company size:** SMEs to mid-market (5–500 employees).
- **Primary geography:** Bulgaria (AOP portal), EU-wide (TED portal, EU grant portals).
- **Verticals:** IT services, construction, consulting, research institutes, NGOs, municipalities.

---

## 4. Success Criteria

### 4.1 User-Facing Success Metrics

| Scenario | Target |
|----------|--------|
| Opportunities loaded into platform | 500+ (AOP + TED combined) |
| Search → opportunity detail flow | ≤ 3 clicks |
| AI summary generation time (100-page document) | < 30 seconds |
| First proposal draft generation | < 2 minutes |
| End-to-end flow (registration → opportunity → proposal) | Completable in one session |

### 4.2 Platform Quality Gates

- 99.5% uptime SLA for the client platform
- REST API p95 latency < 200ms; SSE TTFB < 500ms
- Minimum 80% automated test coverage
- Zero high-severity security findings at GA

---

## 5. User Journeys

### 5.1 Core Journey: Discover → Analyse → Propose → Submit

```
1. Register / Log in
   └─▶ 14-day Professional trial activated automatically

2. Discover Opportunities
   └─▶ Browse searchable, AI-matched list of tenders (AOP, TED, EU grants)
       Filters: CPV sector, region, budget, deadline, match score
       Free tier: name + deadline + location visible
       Paid tier: full details + AI analysis

3. Analyse Tender
   └─▶ Upload tender package (PDF/DOCX/ZIP)
       AI extracts: requirements, deadlines, evaluation criteria, financial thresholds
       AI generates: executive summary, compliance checklist, risk-flagged clauses
       Bid/no-bid AI recommendation → team reviews → override with justification

4. Plan & Allocate
   └─▶ Create proposal workspace
       Assign team roles (bid manager, technical writer, financial analyst, legal)
       Generate task list with deadlines and dependencies
       Configure approval stages

5. Draft Proposal
   └─▶ AI generates first draft from tender requirements + company profile
       Team edits in Tiptap rich-text editor (section locking, threaded comments)
       Version control with diff and rollback
       Reusable content blocks (boilerplate sections)

6. Validate & Finalise
   └─▶ Compliance checker validates against assigned regulatory framework
       ESPD auto-fill from company profile vault
       Scoring simulator predicts evaluator scores and suggests improvements
       Management approval workflow sign-off

7. Export & Submit
   └─▶ Export as PDF and/or DOCX
       Platform provides portal-specific submission guides
       Outcome recorded (won/lost/withdrawn) → feeds analytics

8. Learn & Improve
   └─▶ Analytics: win rate trends, team performance, ROI tracker
       Lessons-learned report generated by AI post-outcome
       Data feeds future AI matching and draft quality
```

### 5.2 Grant Journey (EU Grants specialisation)

```
1. Grant Eligibility Check
   └─▶ Company/municipality profile mapped against active EU programmes
       (Horizon Europe, Digital Europe, structural funds, CAP, Interreg)

2. Budget Construction
   └─▶ AI budget builder: EU cost categories, overhead, co-financing rules

3. Consortium Assembly
   └─▶ Consortium finder: partner suggestions from similar-grant participation data

4. Application Drafting
   └─▶ Logframe generator: logical frameworks, work packages, Gantt, deliverables
       Reporting template generator: periodic report and financial statement templates
```

### 5.3 Admin Journey

```
1. Platform Admin logs in via VPN-restricted admin portal
2. Manages tenants: view, activate, deactivate, adjust subscription tier
3. Manages crawlers: trigger manual runs, view history, configure schedules
4. Manages compliance frameworks: create/edit ZOP, EU directive, programme rule sets
5. Assigns frameworks to opportunities; confirms/overrides AI framework suggestions
6. Configures white-label for Enterprise clients (subdomain, logo, brand, email)
7. Views platform analytics: signup funnel, tier conversion, churn
8. Exports audit log for compliance evidence
```

---

## 6. Domain Requirements

### 6.1 Regulatory Landscape

| Regulation | Impact |
|------------|--------|
| Bulgarian ZOP (Public Procurement Act) | Compliance framework for Bulgarian tenders; ESPD requirement |
| EU Directive 2014/24/EU | Open Procedure rules for EU-funded tenders on TED |
| EU Grant Programme Rules | Horizon Europe, Digital Europe, structural funds, Interreg cost eligibility |
| GDPR | Data residency in EU; right to erasure; DPAs with KraftData |
| eIDAS | Digital signatures deferred to post-MVP |

### 6.2 Compliance Framework System

The platform maintains a database of compliance frameworks. Each opportunity is tagged with the applicable framework. The compliance checker validates proposals against the specific framework assigned to that opportunity — not a generic ruleset. Platform admins own framework creation and assignment. The AI suggests the applicable framework based on the opportunity's country, source, and funding type; the admin confirms or overrides.

---

## 7. Innovation Patterns

### 7.1 AI-First Architecture

All document intelligence and proposal generation flows through the KraftData AI platform:

- Purpose-built agents (document parser, executive summary, clause risk, scoring simulator, pricing assistant, grant eligibility, budget builder, logframe generator, regulation tracker)
- Multi-agent teams for coordinated complex workflows
- RAG (retrieval-augmented generation) via vector storage resources (sector templates, past proposals, regulatory texts)
- Persistent session contexts for multi-turn interactions
- KraftData eval runs for continuous quality monitoring

### 7.2 Streaming-First UX

All user-facing AI operations use Server-Sent Events (SSE) streaming. Users see AI output as it is generated — no blocking waits. The frontend uses native `fetch` + `ReadableStream` (not EventSource, which is GET-only) for streaming POST responses.

### 7.3 Collaborative Proposal Editor

The proposal editor (Tiptap rich-text) supports simultaneous multi-user editing with pessimistic section locking (one editor per section, 15-min TTL), threaded comments anchored to section + version, version control with diff and rollback, and an AI co-pilot generating content in context.

---

## 8. Scope

### 8.1 In-Scope (MVP)

- Opportunity intelligence: Bulgaria (AOP) + EU (TED) + EU grant portals
- AI document analysis and proposal generation
- EU grant specialisation (Horizon Europe, Digital Europe, structural funds, Interreg)
- Compliance framework management (ZOP, EU directives, programme rules)
- Email alert digests (immediate/daily/weekly)
- Calendar sync: Google Calendar + Outlook (OAuth2)
- Analytics dashboards (market intelligence, ROI, team performance, competitor intel)
- Stripe subscription billing (Free, Starter, Professional, Enterprise tiers)
- White-label configuration for Enterprise clients
- Admin portal (VPN-restricted)
- Enterprise API (OpenAPI-documented REST for Enterprise tier clients)
- Bilingual UI: Bulgarian (default) + English

### 8.2 Out-of-Scope (Post-MVP)

- Electronic bid submission (e-procurement portal integration)
- Microsoft OAuth2 social login
- ERP/CRM integration
- Slack/Teams in-app notifications
- Digital signatures (eIDAS)
- Consultant marketplace
- Additional national procurement portals (beyond AOP + TED)
- Additional UI languages beyond BG/EN

---

