## 10. Non-Functional Requirements

### 10.1 Performance

| ID | Requirement | Target |
|----|-------------|--------|
| NFR-PERF-01 | REST API p95 latency | < 200ms |
| NFR-PERF-02 | SSE TTFB (streaming endpoint) | < 500ms |
| NFR-PERF-03 | AI executive summary (100-page document) | < 30 seconds |
| NFR-PERF-04 | First proposal draft generation | < 2 minutes |
| NFR-PERF-05 | Full-text search over 10K+ active tenders | < 500ms |
| NFR-PERF-06 | CPU-bound operations (WeasyPrint, python-docx, bcrypt) must run in thread pool executor | Prevents event loop blocking |
| NFR-PERF-07 | Database materialized views refreshed `CONCURRENTLY` | No exclusive lock during refresh |

### 10.2 Availability & Reliability

| ID | Requirement | Target |
|----|-------------|--------|
| NFR-REL-01 | Client platform uptime SLA | 99.5% |
| NFR-REL-02 | AI gateway circuit breaker (outer) wrapping retry with exponential backoff (inner) for all outbound HTTP | Required pattern |
| NFR-REL-03 | Redis fail-open: Redis outage must not block auth, rate limiting, or tier checks | Required |
| NFR-REL-04 | Stripe outbound calls wrapped with E04 two-layer resilience pattern | Required |
| NFR-REL-05 | Celery tasks: narrow `except` clauses; never swallow `celery.exceptions.Retry` | Required |
| NFR-REL-06 | Stuck-task cleanup: Celery Beat job marks stale `in-progress` records FAILED after configurable TTL | Required |
| NFR-REL-07 | At-least-once event delivery via Redis Streams with DLQ; dual-layer idempotency (DB constraint + Redis SETNX) | Required |

### 10.3 Security

| ID | Requirement | Target |
|----|-------------|--------|
| NFR-SEC-01 | JWT RS256 authentication; tokens validated for signature + expiry | Required |
| NFR-SEC-02 | TLS 1.3 in transit; AES-256 at rest | Required |
| NFR-SEC-03 | Bcrypt password hashing (cost=12); max_length=128 on all password fields | Required |
| NFR-SEC-04 | All webhook signatures validated with `hmac.compare_digest()` — timing-safe | Required |
| NFR-SEC-05 | Cross-tenant isolation: every company-scoped endpoint must have a negative test (Company A → Company B resource → 403) | Required |
| NFR-SEC-06 | Two-tier RBAC enforcement: company role ceiling + entity-level permission (cannot exceed ceiling) | Required |
| NFR-SEC-07 | OAuth state parameter validated against session nonce to prevent CSRF | Required |
| NFR-SEC-08 | `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` usage requires explicit security review comment | Required |
| NFR-SEC-09 | Refresh token rotation with `SELECT FOR UPDATE` pessimistic locking | Required |
| NFR-SEC-10 | IP allowlist middleware on admin API (VPN-restricted) | Required |
| NFR-SEC-11 | Enterprise API keys: SHA-256 hash only stored in DB; full key shown once at creation | Required |

### 10.4 Scalability

| ID | Requirement | Target |
|----|-------------|--------|
| NFR-SCALE-01 | Support 10K+ active tenders with full-text search | Required |
| NFR-SCALE-02 | Support concurrent AI agent execution per tenant | Required |
| NFR-SCALE-03 | Redis Streams consumer group with consumer-group-level parallelism | Required |
| NFR-SCALE-04 | SSE semaphore-controlled concurrency (max 10 concurrent streams per pod) | Required |

### 10.5 Data & Compliance

| ID | Requirement | Target |
|----|-------------|--------|
| NFR-DATA-01 | All data stored within EU (AWS eu-central-1 or equivalent) | Required |
| NFR-DATA-02 | GDPR: right to erasure, data processing records, DPAs with KraftData | Required |
| NFR-DATA-03 | Schema isolation: one PostgreSQL database, six schemas (client, admin, pipeline, gateway, notification, shared) | Required |
| NFR-DATA-04 | No cross-schema queries in application code | Required |
| NFR-DATA-05 | Document retention: opportunity lifetime + 2 years (configurable per tenant) | Required |

