## 11. Feature-Level User Stories

Stories are expressed at feature level, cross-referenced to epics. Story-level breakdowns live in the individual epic files.

### 11.1 Authentication & Organisation

| Story | As a... | I want to... | So that... |
|-------|---------|--------------|------------|
| US-AUTH-01 | New user | Register with email/password and verify my email | I can securely access the platform |
| US-AUTH-02 | Existing user | Log in with Google OAuth2 | I can access the platform without managing another password |
| US-AUTH-03 | Company admin | Invite team members by email and assign roles | I can control who can do what in my organisation |
| US-AUTH-04 | User | Log in and have my session persist securely across browser refreshes | I don't need to re-authenticate constantly |

### 11.2 Opportunity Discovery

| Story | As a... | I want to... | So that... |
|-------|---------|--------------|------------|
| US-OPP-01 | Bid manager | Browse a curated list of tenders from AOP and TED filtered by CPV, region, and budget | I quickly identify relevant opportunities |
| US-OPP-02 | Bid manager | See an AI-computed match score (0–100) against my company profile for each opportunity | I can prioritise which tenders to pursue |
| US-OPP-03 | Free tier user | See basic opportunity details (name, deadline, location, type, status) | I can evaluate the platform before subscribing |
| US-OPP-04 | Paid user | Access full opportunity details including budget, evaluation criteria, and AI analysis | I have all the information I need to make a bid decision |
| US-OPP-05 | Bid manager | Set up configurable email alerts by CPV sector, region, and budget range | I'm notified of new relevant tenders without manually checking |
| US-OPP-06 | Bid manager | Subscribe to an iCal feed of my tracked opportunity deadlines | I can see bid deadlines in my preferred calendar app |
| US-OPP-07 | Paid user | Sync opportunity deadlines with Google Calendar or Outlook | My bid schedule is integrated with my daily workflow |

### 11.3 Document Intelligence

| Story | As a... | I want to... | So that... |
|-------|---------|--------------|------------|
| US-DOC-01 | Bid manager | Upload a tender package (PDF/DOCX/ZIP) and receive an AI-generated executive summary within 30 seconds | I can quickly assess a complex tender without reading 200 pages |
| US-DOC-02 | Legal reviewer | See AI-flagged high-risk clauses (unlimited liability, IP assignment, penalties) in a tender contract | I can prioritise my legal review on the most critical clauses |
| US-DOC-03 | Technical writer | View an auto-generated compliance checklist of every mandatory requirement | I have a structured checklist to track compliance during drafting |
| US-DOC-04 | Company admin | Have ESPD fields pre-filled from the company profile vault | I avoid re-entering the same company data for every tender |

### 11.4 Bid Strategy

| Story | As a... | I want to... | So that... |
|-------|---------|--------------|------------|
| US-BID-01 | Bid manager | Receive an AI bid/no-bid recommendation with a score breakdown | I can make an informed go/no-go decision quickly |
| US-BID-02 | Bid manager | Override an AI recommendation with a written justification | I retain human decision authority while keeping a traceable record |
| US-BID-03 | Bid manager | Record bid outcomes (won/lost/withdrawn) with evaluator feedback | I can build a history that improves future recommendations |
| US-BID-04 | Financial analyst | Get a competitive pricing suggestion based on historical awards | I can price competitively without starting from a blank sheet |

### 11.5 Collaborative Proposal Drafting

| Story | As a... | I want to... | So that... |
|-------|---------|--------------|------------|
| US-PROP-01 | Bid manager | Create a proposal workspace, assign roles to team members, and generate an AI first draft | I can kick off proposal development in minutes |
| US-PROP-02 | Technical writer | Edit proposal sections in a rich-text editor with an AI co-pilot | I can produce high-quality content faster |
| US-PROP-03 | Bid manager | Lock sections while I edit them and see who is editing which section | I avoid overwriting colleagues' work |
| US-PROP-04 | Reviewer | Leave threaded comments on specific sections anchored to a version | I can give structured feedback that the author can action |
| US-PROP-05 | Bid manager | Roll back to a previous proposal version | I can recover from mistakes or bad AI suggestions |
| US-PROP-06 | Technical writer | Reuse pre-approved boilerplate content blocks (company overview, quality management) | I avoid duplicating effort across proposals |
| US-PROP-07 | Bid manager | Export the final proposal as a PDF and DOCX | I can submit to procurement portals in the required format |

### 11.6 Compliance & Review

| Story | As a... | I want to... | So that... |
|-------|---------|--------------|------------|
| US-COMP-01 | Bid manager | Run a compliance check of my draft proposal against the assigned regulatory framework | I catch compliance gaps before submission |
| US-COMP-02 | Bid manager | See a scoring simulator showing predicted evaluator scores per criterion | I can improve the proposal strategically to maximise points |
| US-COMP-03 | Company admin | Request management sign-off through a configurable multi-stage approval workflow | I have an audit trail of approvals before submission |
| US-COMP-04 | Platform admin | Create and edit compliance frameworks (ZOP, EU directive rule sets) | I keep the compliance knowledge base current |
| US-COMP-05 | Bid manager | Be notified by AI when procurement regulations that affect my active bids change | I'm never caught off-guard by regulatory updates |

### 11.7 Grant Specialisation

| Story | As a... | I want to... | So that... |
|-------|---------|--------------|------------|
| US-GRANT-01 | Company admin | Check my organisation's eligibility against active EU grant programmes | I know which programmes I should pursue |
| US-GRANT-02 | Bid manager | Build an EU-compliant budget using the AI budget builder | I ensure cost categories, overhead rates, and co-financing requirements are met |
| US-GRANT-03 | Bid manager | Find potential consortium partners with relevant EU grant experience | I can assemble a strong consortium quickly |
| US-GRANT-04 | Technical writer | Generate a logical framework (logframe), work packages, and Gantt chart from a narrative description | I produce structured grant application components efficiently |

### 11.8 Analytics

| Story | As a... | I want to... | So that... |
|-------|---------|--------------|------------|
| US-ANA-01 | Bid manager | See market intelligence dashboards (procurement volumes, active authorities, seasonal trends) | I can identify the best market segments to target |
| US-ANA-02 | Company admin | Track the ROI of bid preparation (time invested vs. contract value won) | I can justify the bid budget and resource allocation |
| US-ANA-03 | Company admin | View team performance metrics (win rate, bids submitted, average prep time per person) | I can identify coaching opportunities and top performers |
| US-ANA-04 | Bid manager | See competitor intelligence (bidding patterns, win rates, pricing) | I can position our bids to beat specific competitors |
| US-ANA-05 | Company admin | Generate and export management reports (pipeline value, success rates, upcoming deadlines) | I can report to leadership without manual data assembly |
| US-ANA-06 | User | See my current billing period usage vs. tier limits | I know how much AI capacity I have remaining this month |

### 11.9 Subscription & Billing

| Story | As a... | I want to... | So that... |
|-------|---------|--------------|------------|
| US-BILL-01 | New user | Get a 14-day Professional tier trial without a credit card | I can evaluate premium features before committing |
| US-BILL-02 | Free user | Upgrade to a paid tier via Stripe Checkout | I can access premium features with a familiar, secure payment flow |
| US-BILL-03 | Paid user | Manage my subscription (upgrade, downgrade, cancel, update payment method) via a self-service portal | I control my subscription without contacting support |
| US-BILL-04 | Enterprise user | Receive a custom invoice with NET 30/60 terms | I can use standard B2B procurement processes |
| US-BILL-05 | User | Be prompted to upgrade when I hit a monthly AI usage limit | I understand the limit and have a clear path to remove it |

### 11.10 Admin Platform

| Story | As a... | I want to... | So that... |
|-------|---------|--------------|------------|
| US-ADMIN-01 | Platform admin | Manage tenant companies (view, activate, deactivate, change tier) | I can administer the platform at scale |
| US-ADMIN-02 | Platform admin | View crawler run history and trigger manual crawls | I can diagnose data freshness issues |
| US-ADMIN-03 | Platform admin | Configure white-label branding for Enterprise clients | I can deliver the white-label value proposition |
| US-ADMIN-04 | Platform admin | Search and export the immutable audit log | I can respond to compliance and support requests |
| US-ADMIN-05 | Enterprise client | Use the EU Solicit REST API with an API key | I can integrate the platform into my own systems |

