## 12. Acceptance Criteria

### 12.1 Authentication & Identity (AC)

**AC-AUTH-01:** A new user can register with email + password, receive a verification email, and access the platform after clicking the verification link.  
**AC-AUTH-02:** A user can log in with Google OAuth2 and is provisioned with an account if none exists.  
**AC-AUTH-03:** Access tokens expire in 15 minutes; refresh tokens rotate automatically; the second concurrent refresh invalidates the token family and logs the user out.  
**AC-AUTH-04:** A deactivated user cannot receive new tokens on login or refresh.  
**AC-AUTH-05:** Rate-limited auth endpoints return `429` with the standard error envelope; Redis `ConnectionError` causes fail-open (no 500).

### 12.2 Opportunity Discovery (AC)

**AC-OPP-01:** New opportunities from AOP and TED appear in the platform within 24 hours of portal publication.  
**AC-OPP-02:** A free tier user sees only: name, deadline, location, type, status. All other fields are gated behind a paywall prompt.  
**AC-OPP-03:** A paid user can filter opportunities by CPV code, region, min/max budget, deadline range, and status in ≤ 3 clicks from the dashboard.  
**AC-OPP-04:** An AI match score (0–100) is displayed on the listing card and opportunity detail for authenticated users with a company profile.  
**AC-OPP-05:** A user can upload a PDF/DOCX/ZIP tender package (≤ 100MB per file, ≤ 500MB per package). Files failing ClamAV scan are rejected with a clear error message.  
**AC-OPP-06:** A user can configure email alert preferences (CPV, region, budget, deadline proximity) and receive a digest on their chosen schedule (immediate/daily/weekly).  
**AC-OPP-07:** An iCal subscription URL is unique per user; subscribing in a calendar app shows all tracked opportunity deadlines.  
**AC-OPP-08:** Google Calendar sync creates calendar events for tracked deadlines; updating a deadline in EU Solicit updates the calendar event; removing a tracked opportunity deletes the event.

### 12.3 Document Intelligence (AC)

**AC-DOC-01:** An executive summary for a 100-page PDF is generated and streamed to the user within 30 seconds of upload completion.  
**AC-DOC-02:** The AI compliance checklist contains every mandatory requirement extracted from the tender package as individually trackable line items.  
**AC-DOC-03:** Clause risk flags identify unlimited-liability, IP-assignment, and penalty clauses with the relevant clause text and a severity label.  
**AC-DOC-04:** ESPD fields are pre-populated from the company profile vault; the user can review and submit without re-entering stored data.  
**AC-DOC-05:** AI outputs are generated in the user's preferred language (BG or EN), regardless of source document language.

### 12.4 Proposal Drafting (AC)

**AC-PROP-01:** A bid manager can create a proposal workspace, assign team members with named roles, and receive an AI-generated first draft via SSE streaming in under 2 minutes.  
**AC-PROP-02:** Two concurrent users editing the same section: the second user sees a "Section locked by [name]" indicator and cannot save changes until the lock expires (15-min TTL) or the holder releases it.  
**AC-PROP-03:** A concurrent edit by two users on different sections completes without data loss.  
**AC-PROP-04:** A user can view the diff between any two proposal versions and roll back to any previous version.  
**AC-PROP-05:** A reviewer can post a threaded comment on a specific section; the author can reply and resolve the comment thread; comments persist across versions.  
**AC-PROP-06:** The proposal is exported as a valid PDF and DOCX with correct formatting within 60 seconds of export request.  
**AC-PROP-07:** Concurrent save by two different users triggers a 409 Conflict response with a structured body; the client displays a conflict resolution dialog.

### 12.5 Compliance & Billing (AC)

**AC-COMP-01:** The compliance checker validates the proposal against the framework assigned to that specific opportunity (not a generic ruleset) and returns a pass/fail per rule with the relevant proposal location.  
**AC-COMP-02:** The scoring simulator returns a score per evaluation criterion with at least one actionable improvement suggestion per criterion scoring below 70%.  
**AC-BILL-01:** A new user's account is automatically on a 14-day Professional trial. After 14 days, if no subscription is created, the account downgrades to Free tier.  
**AC-BILL-02:** A user who hits their monthly AI summary limit sees an upgrade prompt instead of the summary result; no partial AI generation is billed.  
**AC-BILL-03:** A Stripe `invoice.payment_failed` webhook downgrades the subscription to `past_due` status in the database within 60 seconds of the webhook receipt.  
**AC-BILL-04:** A Stripe webhook replayed with the same `stripe_event_id` is idempotently processed (second delivery returns 200 without side effects).

### 12.6 Analytics (AC)

**AC-ANA-01:** Market intelligence charts show sector-level data scoped exclusively to the requesting user's company; cross-tenant data leakage results in a failed test.  
**AC-ANA-02:** A management report can be exported as PDF or DOCX; the S3 signed URL is valid for 24 hours; the file is accessible at the URL.  
**AC-ANA-03:** Tier-gated analytics features return 403 with `{"error": "tier_required", "minimum_tier": "...", "upgrade_url": "/billing"}` for users below the required tier.

### 12.7 Security (AC)

**AC-SEC-01:** A user with Company A credentials attempting to access a Company B resource receives 403 (not 401 or 404).  
**AC-SEC-02:** A webhook with an invalid HMAC signature returns 401/403 within < 1ms difference from a valid-signature request (timing-safe comparison verified by test).  
**AC-SEC-03:** A cross-user-scoped resource access (e.g., accessing another user's notification preference) returns 404, not 403.  
**AC-SEC-04:** An admin with `platform_admin` role accessing the admin API from a non-allowlisted IP receives 403.

