## 13. Technical Constraints (Summary)

These constraints are non-negotiable and shape implementation choices:

| Constraint | Value |
|------------|-------|
| Backend language | Python 3.12+ |
| API framework | FastAPI (async) |
| ORM | SQLAlchemy (async) + Alembic |
| Database | PostgreSQL 16 (6 schemas, schema isolation) |
| Cache / events | Redis 7 (Redis Streams, no Celery for events) |
| Worker tasks | Celery (for long-running async jobs) |
| Frontend | Next.js 14 App Router, TypeScript strict |
| State management | Zustand (persist + devtools) |
| Data fetching | TanStack Query v5 + `<QueryGuard>` |
| Forms | React Hook Form + Zod (`useZodForm`) |
| UI components | shadcn/ui in `packages/ui` |
| Rich text editor | Tiptap |
| i18n | next-intl v3 (`locales: ['bg', 'en']`, `defaultLocale: 'bg'`) |
| AI platform | KraftData (agents, teams, workflows, RAG) |
| Payment | Stripe (subscriptions, usage metering, customer portal, tax) |
| Email | SendGrid |
| Storage | S3-compatible (MinIO locally; AWS S3 in production) |
| Monitoring | Prometheus `/metrics`, structlog |
| Infrastructure | Docker Compose (local), Helm 3, Terraform ≥ 1.5, GitHub Actions CI |
| Data residency | EU only (AWS eu-central-1 or equivalent) |

